@{fg fill}15-Apr-00  @{fg highlight}V1.8.14@{fg text}
   * Fixed a bug in a Kepler formula. In a strange case this lead to chaotic coordinates
     of asteroids during a short time period. This only was watched only once.
   * Bumped version number of English guide.
   * Again a speed improvement of trigonometric calculations in the 040 version.

@{fg fill}06-Apr-00  @{fg highlight}V1.8.13@{fg text}
   * Improved speed of texture drawing (040 version).
   * Because of a strange rounding mistake of the FPU it could happen, that a centered
     object did not appear on the screen. This only happened in the 040 version with
     fast-sincos enabled.
   * When the Sun was chosen as observing location, it could happen, that an object's
     phase was not drawn correctly because of a division by zero in position angle
     calculation.

@{fg fill}30-Mar-00  @{fg highlight}V1.8.12@{fg text}
   * Program crashed when trying to select certain planets in the telescope window.
   * Earth's moon grid and texture had different rotation senses.

@{fg fill}20-Mar-00  @{fg highlight}V1.8.11@{fg text}
   * Program can be terminatedwith CTRL-C from CLI.
   * Version 1.8.10 was just a private release.
   * GSC catalog has now its own magnitude setting to select minimum magnitude of stars
     independend from the internal stars.
   * Large speed improvement of GSC catalog. At large zooms, stars can now be drawn
     with seconds !!
   * Faster texture drawing.

@{fg fill}10-Mar-00  @{fg highlight}V1.8.9@{fg text}
   * Speedup of GSC catalog access, especially at large zooms.
   * Asteroid catalog updated.
   * Drawing of NGC catalog and some other Deep-Sky catalogs sometimes crashed.
   * CD-ROM Version 1.8.8 contained a bug in the installer icons.
