@{fg fill}22-Feb-00  @{fg highlight}V1.8.8@{fg text}
   * Rise-Set display of sun and moon in calendar window is now perfect.
   * Timezone was set to +12 for a location entry after adding it to the location list.
   * Update mode is back in the installer.
   * A link in the guide didn't work.

@{fg fill}15-Feb-00  @{fg highlight}V1.8.7@{fg text}
   * Just a little speed improvement when drawing map and drawing textures.
   * Improved accuracy of fast-sincos function at same speed (accuracy < 1e-11).
   * Hyperbel orbits are now better visible.
   * Improved texture buffering. Reduces disk accesses.
   * Improved obliquity formula. Better results over a period of 10000 years.
   * Sun's heliographic grid was most times wrong.
   * Uranian moons didn't orbit around Uranus with activated planetary aberration.
   * A typo-mistake in the source code caused planets appear as dark pixel at large
     field-of-view-angle.
   * Planetographic coordinates were wrong with fastsincos-option enabled.
   * Private release.

@{fg fill}04-Feb-00  @{fg highlight}V1.8.6@{fg text}
   * Grrrmmblll...
     A function that was not changed for ages now crashed because of an unknown reason
     Anyway, if you tried to delete the items in the export list, the computer crashed.
   * Quickselecting observing site with popup list didn't change telescope window.
   * Near eclipses, the Earth's phase was drawn wrong as seen from Moon.
   * Rotation sense of Uranian moons was not correct.

@{fg fill}30-Jan-00  @{fg highlight}V1.8.4@{fg text}
